documentation.description: Anvil was unable to open the log file for writing.
documentation.summary: Unable to access log file.

likely_causes.cause: Not enough space.
fixes: Check if you have enough free space in your storage to create or open a log file

likely_causes.cause: Insufficient permissions.
fixes: Check if you have permissions to write to the log file.

[anvil-halt-10].name: UnexpectedVMBehavior
[anvil-halt-10].message: virtual machine entered unexpected state. Please contact developers and provide transaction details that caused this error. Error description: {problem}

documentation.description: This error is used temporarily instead of panics to provide a better experience for developers. It indicates that the VM entered an unforeseen state during transaction execution.
documentation.summary: The virtual machine encountered an unexpected state.

likely_causes.cause: Internal VM logic error or unforeseen edge case.
fixes: Contact the development team with detailed transaction information.
Review the transaction logic for potential issues.

documentation.description: This error occurs when the bootloader does not have enough gas to continue executing the transaction.
documentation.summary: The bootloader has run out of gas.

likely_causes.cause: Insufficient gas limit set for the transaction.
fixes: Increase the gas limit for the transaction.
Optimize the transaction to consume less gas.

documentation.description: This error is emitted when the validation phase of transaction execution exceeds the allocated gas limit.
documentation.summary: The validation step ran out of gas.

likely_causes.cause: Complex validation logic requiring more gas than allocated.
fixes: Increase the gas limit for the validation step.
Simplify the validation logic to consume less gas.

[anvil-halt-13].name: TooBigGasLimit
[anvil-halt-13].message: Transaction has a too big ergs limit and will not be executed by the server

documentation.description: This error occurs when the gas limit set for the transaction is too large for the server to handle.
documentation.summary: The transaction's gas limit is excessively high.

likely_causes.cause: Setting an unrealistically high gas limit for the transaction.
fixes: Adjust the gas limit to a reasonable value.
Consult the network's gas limit guidelines to set an appropriate limit.

[anvil-halt-14].name: NotEnoughGasProvided
[anvil-halt-14].message: Bootloader did not have enough gas to start the transaction

documentation.description: This error is emitted when the bootloader lacks the necessary gas to begin executing the transaction.
documentation.summary: Insufficient gas provided to initiate the transaction.

likely_causes.cause: Insufficient gas allocated for the transaction initiation.
fixes: Increase the gas provided for the transaction.
Ensure that the gas estimation is accurate before setting the gas limit.

[anvil-halt-15].name: MissingInvocationLimitReached
[anvil-halt-15].message: Tx produced too much cold storage accesses

documentation.description: This error occurs when the transaction makes too many missing invocations to memory, surpassing the allowed limit.
documentation.summary: The transaction exceeded the allowed number of cold storage invocations.

likely_causes.cause: Highly complex transaction with excessive memory accesses.
fixes: Optimize the transaction to reduce the number of memory accesses.
Break down the transaction into smaller, more manageable parts.

[anvil-halt-16].name: FailedToSetL2Block
[anvil-halt-16].message: Failed to set information about the L2 block: {msg}

documentation.description: This error is emitted when the system fails to set the necessary information for the L2 block during transaction execution.
documentation.summary: Unable to set L2 block information.

likely_causes.cause: Invalid L2 block data or internal processing error.
fixes: Verify the L2 block information being set.
Check for any internal processing issues that might prevent setting the L2 block.

[anvil-halt-17].name: FailedToAppendTransactionToL2Block
[anvil-halt-17].message: Failed to append the transaction to the current L2 block: {msg}

documentation.description: This error occurs when the system cannot append the transaction to the ongoing L2 block, possibly due to data inconsistencies or internal errors.
documentation.summary: Failed to add the transaction to the L2 block.

likely_causes.cause: Data inconsistency or corruption in the L2 block.
fixes: Ensure the integrity of the L2 block data.
Retry appending the transaction after verifying the L2 block state.

documentation.description: This error is emitted when the VM experiences a critical failure and panics during transaction execution.
documentation.summary: The virtual machine encountered a panic.

likely_causes.cause: Uncaught exception or critical internal error within the VM.
fixes: Review the transaction for any operations that might cause the VM to panic.
Consult the development team to investigate the VM's internal state.

documentation.description: This error occurs when a custom tracer used during transaction execution decides to abort the process, typically due to specific conditions being met.
documentation.summary: Tracer aborted the transaction execution.

likely_causes.cause: Custom tracer conditions not met or detected an issue.
fixes: Review the tracer's logic to understand why it aborted the execution.
Adjust the tracer conditions if necessary to prevent unnecessary aborts.

documentation.description: This error occurs when the account validation step fails during the verification and execution of a transaction.
documentation.summary: Account validation failed during execution.

likely_causes.cause: Invalid account state or credentials.
fixes: Ensure the account has been properly deployed and initialized.
Verify that the account credentials are correct.

documentation.description: This error is emitted when the system fails to publish the compressed bytecodes during transaction execution.
documentation.summary: Unable to publish compressed bytecodes.

likely_causes.cause: Compression algorithm failure or network issues during publishing.
fixes: Ensure the compression algorithm is functioning correctly.
Verify network connectivity and retry the publishing process.

documentation.description: This error occurs when the transaction's execution fails to satisfy the `block.timestamp` assertion, indicating a discrepancy in the expected timestamp.
documentation.summary: Block timestamp assertion failed during the transaction.

likely_causes.cause: Incorrect block timestamp or transaction timing issues.
fixes: Ensure that the block timestamp is set correctly.
Verify the transaction timing and adjust if necessary.

documentation.description: This error is emitted when the paymaster validation process fails during transaction execution.
documentation.summary: Paymaster validation failed.

likely_causes.cause: Invalid paymaster parameters or insufficient funds.
fixes: Check the paymaster configuration and ensure all parameters are correct.
Ensure the paymaster account has sufficient funds to cover the transaction fees.

documentation.description: This error occurs when the system fails to prepare the paymaster before executing a transaction.
documentation.summary: Pre-paymaster preparation step failed.

likely_causes.cause: Error in setting up pre-paymaster state.
fixes: Verify the pre-paymaster setup process and ensure all prerequisites are met.
Check for any dependencies or configurations that might be missing.

[anvil-halt-4].name: PayForTxFailed
[anvil-halt-4].message: Failed to pay for the transaction: {msg}: {data}

documentation.description: This error is emitted when the system fails to deduct the required fees for executing the transaction.
documentation.summary: Payment for the transaction failed.

likely_causes.cause: Insufficient balance or incorrect payment parameters.
fixes: Ensure the sender has enough balance to cover the transaction fees.
Verify that the payment parameters are correctly specified.

documentation.description: This error occurs when the system cannot mark the necessary factory dependencies required for the transaction.
documentation.summary: Failed to mark factory dependencies during execution.

likely_causes.cause: Dependency resolution issues or corrupted state.
fixes: Check the dependency configurations and ensure all required dependencies are available.
Verify the integrity of the system state to rule out corruption.

documentation.description: This error is emitted when the system cannot deduct the necessary fee for the transaction.
documentation.summary: Charging the transaction fee failed.

likely_causes.cause: Insufficient funds or incorrect fee parameters.
fixes: Ensure the account has sufficient funds to cover the transaction fee.
Verify that the fee parameters are correctly specified.

documentation.description: This error occurs when a transaction is attempted from an address that has not been deployed as an account, meaning the `from` address is just a contract.
documentation.summary: The sender address is not a valid account.

likely_causes.cause: Using a contract address as the sender instead of an account.
fixes: Ensure that the `from` address is a properly deployed account.
Deploy an account if necessary and use its address as the sender.

documentation.description: This error is currently not used and should be removed when refactoring errors.
documentation.summary: An inner transaction error occurred.

likely_causes.cause: Internal transaction processing issue.
fixes: Await error refactoring to address this issue properly.

documentation.description: This error is emitted when the system encounters an unspecified reason for halting.
documentation.summary: An unknown error occurred.

likely_causes.cause: Unexpected or unhandled VM state.
fixes: Contact the developers with transaction details that caused this error.
Review the transaction to identify any anomalies.

documentation.description: This error represents a general VM failure, containing a message and additional data for debugging.
documentation.summary: A general VM error occurred.

likely_causes.cause: An unexpected condition occurred within the VM.
fixes: Review the transaction details and VM logs for more information.
Contact the development team with the error data.

documentation.description: This error is emitted when an inner transaction within the VM fails, typically related to bootloader execution.
documentation.summary: An inner transaction error occurred.

likely_causes.cause: Failure in executing a nested transaction within the VM.
fixes: Check the inner transaction details for errors.
Ensure that all prerequisites for the nested transaction are met.

documentation.description: This error indicates a generic failure within the VM, without specific details.
documentation.summary: A generic VM error.

likely_causes.cause: A non-specific internal error within the VM.
fixes: Review the VM logs for more detailed information.
Contact support with the VM state and error context.

[anvil-revert-4].name: Unknown
[anvil-revert-4].message: Unknown VM revert reason: function_selector={function_selector}, data={data}

documentation.description: This error is emitted when the VM encounters a revert reason that is not recognized, including the function selector and raw data for debugging.
documentation.summary: An unknown VM revert reason was encountered.

likely_causes.cause: Reverting with an unrecognized error type or corrupted data.
fixes: Verify the integrity of the transaction data.
Ensure that the function selectors used in the contract are correct.
Contact the development team with the raw error data.

[anvil-state-1].name: LoadingStateOverExistingStateError
[anvil-state-1].message: Loading state into a node with existing state is not allowed.

documentation.description: It is not allowed to load a state overriding the existing node state. If you have a use case for that, please create an issue.
documentation.summary: It is not allowed to load a state overriding the existing node state.

[anvil-state-2].name: LoadEmptyStateError
[anvil-state-2].message: Loading a state without blocks is not allowed.

documentation.description: It is not allowed to load a state without any blocks in it.
documentation.summary: Attempt to load a state with no blocks

likely_causes.cause: You meant to provide a different state.

[anvil-state-6].name: LoadStateError
[anvil-state-6].message: Error while attempting to access the state located at `{path}`. Reason: {reason}.
